==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apartment house
<hw>A*part"ment house</hw>. <def>A building comprising a number of lving
units (apartments{4}) designed for separate housekeeping tenements, but
having conveniences, such as heat, light, elevator service, etc.,
furnished in common; contrasted to a <er>detached dwelling</er>.
Sometimes distinguished in the United States from a <contr>flat
house</contr>, in which each living unit comprises one entire floor,
whereas in an apartment house a floor may be partitioned into any number
of apartments{4}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apartness</ent>⟦br⟧
